find_outliers <- function(data, numeric_vars) {
  data %>%
    filter(if_any(all_of(numeric_vars), ~ . < mean(.) - 3 * sd(.) | . > mean(.) + 3 * sd(.)))
}

outliers <- find_outliers(cleaned_data, numeric_vars)

write.csv(outliers, "outliers.csv", row.names = FALSE)

statistics <- list(
  ` ` = ~sum(!is.na(.x)) %>% as.character(),
  `  ` = ~sum(is.na(.x)) %>% as.character(),
  `` = ~mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE) %>% round(2) %>% as.character(), 
  `` = ~median(.x, na.rm = TRUE) %>% round(2) %>% as.character(),
  ` ` = ~sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE) %>% round(2) %>% as.character(),
  `25% ` = ~quantile(.x, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE) %>% round(2) %>% as.character(),
  `75% ` = ~quantile(.x, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE) %>% round(2) %>% as.character(),
  `95%  ` = ~round(mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE) - 1.96 * sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(sum(!is.na(.x))), 2) %>% as.character(),
  `95%  ` = ~round(mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE) + 1.96 * sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE) / sqrt(sum(!is.na(.x))), 2) %>% as.character(),
  `` = ~min(.x, na.rm = TRUE) %>% round(2) %>% as.character(),
  `` = ~max(.x, na.rm = TRUE) %>% round(2) %>% as.character()
)

numeric_vars <- c("", "", "", "", "")
factor_vars <- c("", "", "", "", "_", "_")

compare_groups <- function(data, group_var, numeric_vars, categorical_vars) {
  results <- list()
  
  # -   ,   
  for (num_var in numeric_vars) {
    test <- wilcox.test(reformulate(group_var, response = num_var), data = data)
    results[[num_var]] <- tibble(
       = num_var,
       = "-",
      p_value = test$p.value,
      `  ` = ifelse(test$p.value < 0.05, "", "")
    )
  }
  
  #-    , ..  
  for (cat_var in factor_vars) {
    tbl <- table(data[[group_var]], data[[cat_var]])
    test <- chisq.test(tbl)
    results[[cat_var]] <- tibble(
       = cat_var,
       = "-",
      p_value = test$p.value,
      `  ` = ifelse(test$p.value < 0.05, "", "")
    )
  }

  bind_rows(results)
}

results <- compare_groups(cleaned_data2, "__", numeric_vars, factor_vars)
